Let’s be more rigorous, and compute a direct (cf. indirect) estimate of prediction error via k-fold cross validation. Unfortunately, the regsubsets function does not work with the predict function that we have become familiar with. The predict.regsubsets function provided below achieves something comparable to predict (in brief, it extracts the fitted coefficients for each model size and then multiplies the corresponding predictors for each test observations). This code does not need to be edited.

#provided function - do not edit
predict.regsubsets <- function(object, newdata, id, ...) {
  form <- as.formula(object$call[[2]]) #pull out the formula
  mat <- model.matrix(form, newdata) #make a matrix
  coefs <- coef(object, id=id) #pull out coefficients
  vars <- names(coefs) #pull out associated predictors
  mat[, vars] %*% coefs #matrix multiplciation
}
